This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of search bias and uploader characteristics, which are relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories, respectively. The use of statistical methods to analyze the data also suggests the sub-categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Sound (cs.SD) as possible categories.
